# Node.js User Management System

This is a simple Node.js application for managing users. It provides basic functionality to create users, list users, and view user details.

## Features

- Create a new user by submitting a form with a username.
- View a list of all users.
- Each user is stored in a text file (`users.txt`) with one user per line.

## Requirements

- Node.js installed on your machine.

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:
https://github.com/prabha2612/Nodejs_assign1.git

2. Navigate to the project directory:
cd Assign1

## Usage

1. Start the server:
node app.js


2. Open a web browser and navigate to `http://localhost:3000`.

3. You can now create users by visiting `/create` and listing users by visiting `/users`.

## File Structure

- `app.js`: Main entry point of the application. Creates an HTTP server and handles requests.
- `routes.js`: Contains request handling logic. Defines routes for creating users, adding users, and listing users.
- `users.txt`: Text file to store user data.

